    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Members of a superfamily containing around 3,500 species of insects that occur worldwide and are named for their fast, darting flight. Skippers are considered an intermediate form between butterflies and moths.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
